<h3>Precipitation</h3>
Conditions were wetter than average across most of Ireland, northern UK, Scandinavia, Finland, parts of western Russia, as well as large parts of eastern Europe and the Balkans.
A further small region of wet conditions, with above average precipitation is found in the eastern part of the Pyrenees.
<br><br>
In the rest of Europe, conditions were mostly drier than average, especially over northwestern Spain, France and central Germany, as well as regions bordering the Black Sea, and a large region stretching northeastward from the Black Sea.
